### 3.2 Experiment 2B — `fork()` + `exec()` + `wait()` + `exit()`

**Logic Steps:**
1. Parent calls `fork()`.
2. **Child** branch: prints "Running ls…", calls `execlp("ls","ls","-l",NULL)`. If `execlp` returns, it failed → call `exit(127)`.
3. **Parent** branch: calls `waitpid(pid, &status, 0)` to block until the child finishes.
4. Decodes the status using `WIFEXITED` and `WEXITSTATUS`; prints the result.
5. Returns `0`.

```c
/* Program 2B — fork + exec + wait + exit */
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <unistd.h>
#include <sys/types.h>
#include <sys/wait.h>

int main(void) {
    pid_t pid = fork();

    if (pid < 0) {
        perror("fork"); return EXIT_FAILURE;
    }

    if (pid == 0) {
        /* ===== CHILD ===== */
        printf("[CHILD %d] Executing: ls -l /\n", getpid());
        execlp("ls", "ls", "-l", "/", (char *)NULL);
        /* Reached only if exec fails */
        perror("execlp");
        exit(127);
    } else {
        /* ===== PARENT ===== */
        int status;
        printf("[PARENT %d] Waiting for child %d...\n",
               getpid(), pid);
        waitpid(pid, &status, 0);

        if (WIFEXITED(status)) {
            printf("[PARENT] Child exited normally "
                   "with status %d\n", WEXITSTATUS(status));
        } else if (WIFSIGNALED(status)) {
            printf("[PARENT] Child killed by signal %d\n",
                   WTERMSIG(status));
        }
    }
    return EXIT_SUCCESS;
}
```

**Status-Decoding Derivation (full step-by-step):**

The kernel stores a 32-bit exit status. The low 8 bits hold either the exit code (if `WIFEXITED`) or the signal number (if `WIFSIGNALED`). The macros perform bit-shift operations:

$$
\text{WIFEXITED}(s) \;\Longleftrightarrow\; (s) \text{ is in the W\_EXITED bit range, i.e., } ((s) \& \texttt{0x7f}) == 0
$$

$$
\text{WEXITSTATUS}(s) \;=\; ((s) \gg 8) \;\&\; \texttt{0xff}
$$

$$
\text{WIFSIGNALED}(s) \;\Longleftrightarrow\; ((s) \& \texttt{0x7f}) \neq 0 \;\land\; ((s) \& \texttt{0x40}) == 0
$$

$$
\text{WTERMSIG}(s) \;=\; (s) \;\&\; \texttt{0x7f}
$$

**Explanatory table of `wait()` status bits:**

| Bits 7..0 | Bits 15..8 | Meaning |
|------------|-------------|---------|
| $=0$ | exit code | Normal termination (`WIFEXITED` true) |
| $\neq 0$, bit 6 = 0 | unused | Killed by signal (WTERMSIG = bits 7..0) |
| bit 6 = 1, bit 7 = 0 | unused | Stopped by signal |
| bit 7 = 1, bit 6 = 0 | unused | Continued (SIGCONT) |

