### 3.4 Experiment 2D — `opendir()` + `readdir()` (Recursive `ls`-style Lister)

**Logic Steps:**
1. Take a directory path from `argv[1]` (default `.`).
2. Call `opendir()`. On `NULL`, print `errno` and return.
3. Loop calling `readdir()` until it returns `NULL` (end of stream or error).
4. Skip the `.` and `..` pseudo-entries.
5. For every real entry, build the full path as `path/entry->d_name` and call `stat()`.
6. Print the type tag (`[D]` / `[F]` / `[L]`), permissions, size, and name.
7. Close the directory with `closedir()`.

```c
/* Program 2D — Directory lister using opendir/readdir/stat */
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <dirent.h>
#include <sys/stat.h>
#include <errno.h>

static void list_dir(const char *path) {
    DIR *d = opendir(path);
    if (!d) {
        fprintf(stderr, "opendir(%s): %s\n", path, strerror(errno));
        return;
    }

    struct dirent *e;
    while ((e = readdir(d)) != NULL) {
        /* Skip . and .. */
        if (strcmp(e->d_name, ".") == 0 ||
            strcmp(e->d_name, "..") == 0) continue;

        char full[4096];
        snprintf(full, sizeof(full), "%s/%s", path, e->d_name);

        struct stat sb;
        if (stat(full, &sb) == -1) {
            perror("stat");
            continue;
        }

        char tag = '-';
        if      (S_ISDIR(sb.st_mode)) tag = 'D';
        else if (S_ISLNK(sb.st_mode)) tag = 'L';
        else                           tag = 'F';

        printf("[%c] %04o  %8lld  %s\n",
               tag,
               sb.st_mode & 07777,
               (long long)sb.st_size,
               e->d_name);
    }
    closedir(d);
}

int main(int argc, char *argv[]) {
    const char *path = (argc > 1) ? argv[1] : ".";
    list_dir(path);
    return EXIT_SUCCESS;
}
```

**Sample Output (running `./listdir /etc`):**
```
[D] 0755      4096  acpi
[F] 0644        28  adjtime
[L] 0777         7  alternatives
...
```

**Error-Handling Decision Matrix:**

| `opendir` returns | Reason | Action |
|-------------------|--------|--------|
| Non-NULL `DIR*` | Success | Loop with `readdir` |
| `NULL` and `errno = ENOENT` | Path does not exist | Inform user, exit |
| `NULL` and `errno = EACCES` | No read permission | Inform user, exit |
| `NULL` and `errno = ENOTDIR` | A component is not a directory | Inform user, exit |

