> **Question B — [KTU 2024 Alternative, Module 2]**
> **(a) [7 marks]** Write a C program that accepts a directory path as a command-line argument and lists **only the regular files** (not sub-directories) along with their size and permissions. Use `opendir`, `readdir`, `stat`, and `S_ISREG`.
>
> **(b) [7 marks]** Explain the internal structure of `struct dirent` and `struct stat`. How are file permissions represented in `st_mode`? Demonstrate with a decoded example for mode `0640`.

**Model Solution (a) — 7 marks:**

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <dirent.h>
#include <sys/stat.h>
#include <errno.h>

int main(int argc, char *argv[]) {
    const char *path = (argc > 1) ? argv[1] : ".";
    DIR *d = opendir(path);
    if (!d) { perror("opendir"); return EXIT_FAILURE; }

    struct dirent *e;
    while ((e = readdir(d)) != NULL) {
        if (!strcmp(e->d_name, ".") || !strcmp(e->d_name, "..")) continue;
        char full[4096];
        snprintf(full, sizeof full, "%s/%s", path, e->d_name);

        struct stat sb;
        if (stat(full, &sb) == -1) { perror("stat"); continue; }

        if (S_ISREG(sb.st_mode))
            printf("F  %04o  %8lld  %s\n",
                   sb.st_mode & 07777, (long long)sb.st_size, e->d_name);
    }
    closedir(d);
    return EXIT_SUCCESS;
}
```

**Mark split:**
- 2 marks: Correct `opendir` + loop using `readdir`
- 2 marks: Correct `snprintf` to form full path
- 2 marks: `stat` call + `S_ISREG` filter
- 1 mark: Output formatting

**Model Solution (b) — 7 marks:**

**`struct dirent` key fields (2 marks):**

| Field | Meaning |
|-------|---------|
| `ino_t d_ino` | Inode number of the entry |
| `off_t d_off` | Offset to next `dirent` in stream |
| `unsigned short d_reclen` | Length of this record |
| `unsigned char d_type` | `DT_REG`, `DT_DIR`, `DT_LNK`, … |
| `char d_name[256]` | Null-terminated name |

**`struct stat` key fields (2 marks):**
`st_mode`, `st_ino`, `st_dev`, `st_nlink`, `st_uid`, `st_gid`, `st_size`, `st_atime`, `st_mtime`, `st_ctime`, `st_blksize`, `st_blocks`.

**`st_mode` permission bits (2 marks):**

The low 12 bits of `st_mode` encode permissions. For mode `0640` (octal):

| Bit position | Octal digit | Bits | Symbolic | Meaning |
|-------------|-------------|------|----------|---------|
| 8..6 | 6 | 110 | `rw-` | Owner: read + write |
| 5..3 | 4 | 100 | `r--` | Group: read |
| 2..0 | 0 | 000 | `---` | Others: none |

**Conclusion:** Mode `0640` = `rw-r-----` — owner has read/write, group has read, others have no access.

**Decoding formula (1 mark):**
$$
\text{owner\_bits}  = (m \gg 6) \,\&\, 7
$$

$$
\text{group\_bits}  = (m \gg 3) \,\&\, 7
$$

$$
\text{other\_bits}  =  m \,\&\, 7
$$

