### 5.3 KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning

> [!WARNING]
> **Common Mark-Deduction Pitfalls (cost up to 3–5 marks per question)**
> 1. **Forgetting the `NULL` terminator in `execlp/execl/execle`.** Without `(char *)NULL`, behaviour is undefined and most examiners deduct 1 full mark.
> 2. **Using `exit(0)` inside the child after a successful `exec`.** Once `exec` succeeds, that line is never reached — examiners flag this as showing conceptual confusion (−1 mark).
> 3. **Not checking the return value of `fork`.** Always test for $-1$.
> 4. **Mixing `S_IFREG` bit-tests instead of using the `S_ISREG` macro.** While both work, the macro is portable and is what the KTU answer key expects.
> 5. **Forgetting to call `closedir`.** Memory leak; −1 mark in the viva.
> 6. **Printing "PID = 0" for the child without explaining why.** Examiners want the explanation: *"the kernel returns 0 to the child so it can recognize its own role."*
> 7. **Wrong header inclusions.** `<sys/types.h>` must be included for `pid_t`; `<sys/wait.h>` for `WEXITSTATUS`.

---

### 5.4 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember (Rapid-Revision Checklist)

- [ ] `fork()` returns **twice** — child gets 0, parent gets child PID; failure → $-1$.
- [ ] After `exec()` succeeds, the function **does not return**; the calling image is replaced.
- [ ] `execlp` / `execvp` search `$PATH`; `execv` / `execl` require **absolute** path.
- [ ] `getpid` → own PID; `getppid` → parent's PID (1 if re-parented to init).
- [ ] Always pair `exit(0)` (or return) with `wait`/`waitpid` in the parent to **avoid zombies**.
- [ ] `WIFEXITED`, `WEXITSTATUS`, `WIFSIGNALED`, `WTERMSIG` are the four **must-know** status macros.
- [ ] `close(fd)` releases the descriptor; subsequent I/O returns `EBADF`.
- [ ] `struct stat` permissions live in the **low 12 bits** of `st_mode`; use `S_ISREG`, `S_ISDIR`, `S_ISLNK` for type tests.
- [ ] `opendir` returns `DIR*`; `readdir` returns `struct dirent*`; loop until `NULL`; always `closedir`.
- [ ] Skip `.` and `..` in `readdir` loops to prevent infinite recursion.
- [ ] Headers cheat sheet: `<unistd.h>` (fork/exec/getpid/close), `<sys/wait.h>` (wait), `<sys/stat.h>` (stat), `<dirent.h>` (opendir/readdir), `<stdlib.h>` (exit).
- [ ] Compile with `gcc -Wall -Wextra -o prog prog.c` as per the KTU 2024 lab manual.
